04484nam a22007095i 9783110897029DE-B159720221004111318.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221004t20132004gw     fo  d z      mul d  a(OCoLC)979640579  a97831108970297 a10.1515/97831108970292doi  a(DE-B1597)56178  a(OCoLC)865508180  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 amul  agwcDE 4aBS1721b2004eb 7aREL0060902bisacsh04a229/.220422204aThe Book of Tobit :bTexts from the Principal Ancient and Medieval Traditions. With Synopsis, Concordances, and Annotated Texts in Aramaic, Hebrew, Greek, Latin, and Syriac /cStuart Weeks, Simon Gathercole, Loren Stuckenbruck.  aReprint 2013 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter, c[2013] 4c©2004  a1 online resource (792 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aFontes et Subsidia ad Bibliam pertinentes ,x1861-602X ;v300tFrontmatter -- tForeword -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tSynopsis -- tNotes to the Synopsis -- tGreek Concordance -- tLatin Concordance -- tHebrew Concordance -- tAramaic Concordance -- tAppendix0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas Verhältnis der vielen verschiedenen Versionen und Rezensionen des Tobitbuches ist ein notorisches Problem für die Textkritik und die Geschichte des antiken Judentums. Das Fehlen einer verlässlichen Textzusammenstellung erschwert eine Untersuchung dieses Problems. In diesem Band werden erstmals die maßgeblichen griechischen, lateinischen, hebräischen, aramäischen und syrischen Versionen (manche bislang übersehen oder praktisch unzugänglich) zusammengestellt und teilweise mit verbesserten Lesarten geboten. Ein einheitliches Verszählungssystem und die synoptische Darstellung der wichtigsten Versionen erleichtern den Vergleich. Mit Einführungen, kritischem Apparat, Kommentaren zum Verhältnis der Versionen und ausführlichen Konkordanzen.  aThe relationships between the many different versions of Tobit present a famous and important problem for text-critics and historians of Judaism; however, study of the subject has been hindered by the lack of any single, reliable collection. This book brings together, for the first time, a wide range of texts (Greek, Latin, Hebrew, Aramaic, Syriac), some previously overlooked or virtually inaccessible, based in many cases on new readings. A single system of verse numeration is applied to all, and the key versions are presented synoptically, to facilitate comparison. Introductions and critical notes are provided for each text, along with succinct observations on the relationships between them in each passage, and concordances to assist stylistic and linguistic study.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Multiple languages.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aBuch. 4aKonkordanz. 4aTextkritik. 4aTobit. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh1 aGathercole, Simon, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStuckenbruck, Loren, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWeeks, Stuart, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR0 cprintz978311017676640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311089702940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110897029423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110897029/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014